                              "cell_type": "markdown",
                              "metadata": {},
                              "source": [
                                        "### Interpretations of the results \n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "At first we were confused because CentralAir has the biggest coefficient (+22%) \n",
                                        "but GrLivArea has the highest F-statistic (619), so which one is more important ?\n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "After thinking about it we realized they don't measure the same thing :\n",
                                        "- CentralAir goes from 0 to 1, so one step already gives +22%. thats a lot per unit.\n",
                                        "- GrLivArea only adds +0.03% per sq.ft. which seems nothing, but houses vary a lot in size so the total effect is actually huge.\n",
                                        "- same logic for OverallQual, it goes from 1 to 10 so +8.46% per level adds up fast.\n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "First lets look at how much each feature actually varies in the dataset :\n",
                                        "- GrLivArea   : 95% of houses are between 784 and 2662 sq.ft.  (range = 1878 sq.ft.)\n",
                                        "- OverallQual : 95% of houses are between quality 4 and 9   (range = 5 levels)\n",
                                        "- CentralAir  : 93.5% of houses have AC and only 6.5% dont  (barely any variation)\n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "Then using $e^{coef \\times range} - 1$ to get the realistic total effect :\n",
                                        "- GrLivArea   : $e^{0.0003 \\times 1878} - 1$ = **+76%**\n",
                                        "- OverallQual : $e^{0.0812 \\times 5} - 1$ = **+50%**\n",
                                        "- CentralAir  : $e^{0.1998 \\times 1} - 1$ = **+22%**\n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "So GrLivArea now has the biggest total effect (+76%) AND the highest F-statistic (619).\n",
                                        "After removing the outliers (huge houses sold cheap), the signal from GrLivArea became\n",
                                        "much cleaner and its real impact is now fully visible.\n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "The F-statistic measures signal vs noise (F = variance explained / residual variance).\n",
                                        "GrLivArea is a physical and objective measure, every sq.ft. contributes consistently \n",
                                        "to the price so the model makes very small errors with it. Low noise = high F.\n",
                                        "\n",
                                        "OverallQual is a subjective score from 1 to 10. Not all quality-7 houses are worth \n",
                                        "the same price, so grouping them together creates more unexplained variation (noise). \n",
                                        "More noise = lower F-statistic, even if the total impact is still significant (+50%).\n",
                                        "\n",
