    "### Interpretation of Residual Plots\n",
    "\n",
    "**Plot 1 - Residuals vs Fitted** : the points are mostly around 0 which means the model \n",
    "is not really biased. The spread looks more homogeneous now that we removed the extreme outliers.\n",
    "Overall the model is not really biased.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Plot 2 - Q-Q Plot** : most points follow the red line so the residuals are roughly normal. \n",
    "There is still some deviation at the bottom left which shows the distribution is slightly left-skewed,\n",
    "but it is much better than before removing the outliers.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Plot 3 - Residuals Distribution** : looks like a bell curve centered on 0 which is good. \n",
    "It is slightly skewed to the left but overall the normality assumption holds reasonably well.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Conclusion** : the residuals are approximately normal and centered on 0. \n",
    "After cleaning the data, \n",
    "the model improved from R² = 0.816 to R² = 0.832."
