   "source": [
    "### Interpretations of the results \n",
    "\n",
    "After the log-transform, GrLivArea now has the biggest coefficient (0.4322) and the highest F-statistic (624). So at this point its clear that its the most important feature.\n",
    "\n",
    "Our first instinct was to just rank the features by their coefficient, but then we realized that doesnt really make sense because they dont all vary the same amount in the data.\n",
    "\n",
    "We take CentralAir for example, the coefficient is 0.1882 which looks big, but in reality, 93.5% of houses already have AC. So almost every house in the dataset has it, which means the feature barely changes between houses. A feature that doesnt vary cant really explain much even if its coefficient looks large.\n",
    "\n",
    "So we computed the realistic total effect over the actual range of each feature using $e^{coef \\times range} - 1$ :\n",
    "\n",
    "- GrLivArea : log(area) goes from 7 to 8 for 95% of houses → range = 1\n",
    "- OverallQual : quality goes from 4 to 9 for 95% of houses → range = 5\n",
    "- CentralAir : 93.5% already have it → almost no variation\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{GrLivArea}   : e^{0.4322 \\times 1} - 1 = +54\\%$$\n",
    "$$\\text{OverallQual} : e^{0.0847 \\times 5} - 1 = +53\\%$$\n",
    "$$\\text{CentralAir}  : e^{0.1882 \\times 1} - 1 = +21\\%$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Honestly we didnt expect GrLivArea and OverallQual to be that close (+54% vs +53%). But GrLivArea still has a way higher F-statistic (624 vs 212), and we think its because living area is something concrete and objective, every sq.ft. adds value in a predictable way so the model makes fewer errors. OverallQual is more subjective, two houses rated 7 can sell at very different prices depending on things the score doesnt capture, so there is more noise.\n",
    "\n",
    "we cant just look at the coefficient alone. We have to also check how much the feature actually varies in the data and how consistently the model predicts from it. After the log-transform GrLivArea is clearly the strongest feature on all of these criteria."
